<p><b>Sephardi Jews</b> (<a href="/wiki/Hebrew_language" title="Hebrew language">Hebrew</a>: <span lang="he" dir="rtl" xml:lang="he"><b>ספרדי</b></span>‎, <small><a href="/wiki/Hebrew_language#Modern_Hebrew" title="Hebrew language">Standard</a></small> <i><span class="Unicode">Səfardi</span></i> <small><a href="/wiki/Tiberian_vocalization" title="Tiberian vocalization">Tiberian</a></small> <i><span class="Unicode">Səp̄arədî</span></i>; plural <b>ספרדים</b>, <small><a href="/wiki/Hebrew_language#Modern_Hebrew" title="Hebrew language">Standard</a></small> <i><span class="Unicode">Səfaradim</span></i> <small><a href="/wiki/Tiberian_vocalization" title="Tiberian vocalization">Tiberian</a></small> <i><span class="Unicode">Səp̄arədîm</span></i>; <a href="/wiki/Spanish_language" title="Spanish language">Spanish</a> <i><span class="Unicode">Sefardíes</span></i>; <a href="/wiki/Portuguese_language" title="Portuguese language">Portuguese</a> <i><span class="Unicode">Sefarditas</span></i>, <a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">Greek</a> <i><span class="Unicode">Σεφάρδοι</span></i>, <a href="/wiki/Turkish_language" title="Turkish language">Turkish</a> <i><span class="Unicode">Sefarad</span></i>, <a href="/wiki/Judaeo-Spanish_language" title="Judaeo-Spanish language" class="mw-redirect">Judaeo-Spanish</a> <i>Sefardies</i>) are a subgroup of <a href="/wiki/Jew" title="Jew">Jews</a> originating in the <a href="/wiki/Iberian_Peninsula" title="Iberian Peninsula">Iberian Peninsula</a> and <a href="/wiki/North_Africa" title="North Africa">North Africa</a>, usually defined in contrast to <a href="/wiki/Ashkenazi" title="Ashkenazi" class="mw-redirect">Ashkenazi</a> or <a href="/wiki/Mizrahi_Jews" title="Mizrahi Jews">Mizrahi Jews</a>.</p>
