<li><a href="http://faur.derushah.com/articlesbyhakhamjosefaur.html#enlightenment%22" class="external text" title="http://faur.derushah.com/articlesbyhakhamjosefaur.html#enlightenment%22" rel="nofollow">Sepharadi Thought in the Presence of the European Enlightenment</a> by Jose Faur, identifying the difference in reaction to the European Enlightenment among Sepharadi and Ashkenazi communities</li>
<li><a href="http://faur.derushah.com/articlesbyhakhamjosefaur.html#semitism" class="external text" title="http://faur.derushah.com/articlesbyhakhamjosefaur.html#semitism" rel="nofollow">Anti-Semitism in the Sepharadi Mind</a> by Jose Faur, describing the cultural response of Sepharadim to anti-Semitism</li>
<li><a href="http://sefarad.revistas.csic.es" class="external text" title="http://sefarad.revistas.csic.es" rel="nofollow">Sefarad</a>, Journal on Hebraic, Sephardim and Middle East Studies, <a href="http://www.filol.csic.es" class="external text" title="http://www.filol.csic.es" rel="nofollow">ILC</a>, <a href="/wiki/CSIC" title="CSIC" class="mw-redirect">CSIC</a> (scientific articles in Spanish, English and other languages)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.saulsilasfathi.com" class="external text" title="http://www.saulsilasfathi.com" rel="nofollow">Saul Silas Fathi</a> Full Circle: Escape From Baghdad and the Return by Saul Silas Fathi, A prominent Iraqi Jewish family's escape from persecution.</li>
</ul>
